<P>THE
Ingenious and Diverting
LETTERS
OF THE
Lady'<HI>s</HI>&mdash;TRAVELS
INTO
SPAIN.</P>
<P>DESCRIBING
The Devotions, Nunneries, Humour,
Cu&s;toms, Laws, Militia, Trade, Diet,
and Recreations of that People.</P>
<P>Intermixt with
Great Variety of Modern Adventures, and
Surpri&s;ing Accidents: being the True&s;t and Be&s;t
REMARKS Extant on that Court and Country.</P>
<P>The Sixth Edition, with the Addition of a Letter
of the State of <HI>SPAIN,</HI> as it was in the Year
1700. Never before in <HI>Engli&s;h.</HI></P>
<P>In Three PARTS.</P>
<P><HI>LONDON:</HI>
Printed for and &s;old by <HI>Samue$ Cro$ch</HI> at the corner of
